JOHANNESBURG – The Department of Home Affairs has detained four foreign nationals at the ANN7 offices in Midrand on Tuesday. Home Affairs spokesperson, Mayihlome Tshwete confirmed that a raid had taken place at the broadcaster's office. READ: Home Affairs inspects ANN7 offices “We have detained, I believe, four people who don't have the necessary documentation,” said Tshwete. Home Affairs says it was acting on information it had received. The department had previously conducted an inspection at ANN7. eNCA